1
00:00:00,445 --> 00:00:05,565
The Anchored VWAP is one of the best 
tools for finding potential entry points,  

2
00:00:05,565 --> 00:00:09,645
especially in the stock market.
While the traditional VWAP starts  

3
00:00:09,645 --> 00:00:14,205
from the beginning of the trading 
day to its end, the Anchored VWAP  

4
00:00:14,205 --> 00:00:20,045
allows you to choose your starting point.
This flexibility is a game-changer, as it  

5
00:00:20,045 --> 00:00:27,005
lets you align the indicator with a significant 
market event or at psychological turning points.
  

6
00:00:27,005 --> 00:00:32,765
So we’ll anchor the VWAP at a high-volume 
bar, and this way, you can track how the  

7
00:00:32,765 --> 00:00:39,485
market behaves relative to this important level.
High volume often signals strong interest in the  

8
00:00:39,485 --> 00:00:45,805
market, and when combined with a price move, it 
can indicate momentum in a particular direction. 

9
00:00:46,445 --> 00:00:52,205
The core of this strategy revolves around 
trading pullbacks to the VWAP lines,  

10
00:00:52,205 --> 00:00:59,085
when price temporarily moves against the main 
trend, before resuming its original direction. 
  

11
00:00:59,085 --> 00:01:03,645
Selecting the right anchoring 
point is crucial for this strategy. 

12
00:01:03,645 --> 00:01:10,365
Ideally, you want to choose a point that marks 
a clear shift in market structure or psychology. 

13
00:01:10,365 --> 00:01:16,525
This could also be a significant swing 
high or low, or a major news event. 

14
00:01:16,525 --> 00:01:21,245
But a bar with exceptionally 
high volume is something special. 

15
00:01:21,245 --> 00:01:26,925
The goal is to capture a point where the 
market's behavior changed significantly.
  

16
00:01:26,925 --> 00:01:32,125
So in this chart, we anchored the 
VWAP on the highest volume bar. 

17
00:01:32,125 --> 00:01:36,605
This high volume shows increased 
participation from traders,  

18
00:01:36,605 --> 00:01:41,885
often signaling important price 
levels or potential trend changes. 

19
00:01:41,885 --> 00:01:47,085
When this high volume coincides with a 
strong price move, it can be a powerful  

20
00:01:47,085 --> 00:01:52,125
indicator of market direction.
 
Once you've anchored your VWAP,  

21
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:56,685
the strategy involves watching 
for price pullbacks to this line. 

22
00:01:56,685 --> 00:02:04,125
These pullbacks represent potential entry points 
for trades in the direction of the overall trend. 

23
00:02:04,125 --> 00:02:09,085
For example, in an uptrend, you might 
look for buying opportunities when the  

24
00:02:09,085 --> 00:02:15,165
price pulls back to the Anchored line, or 
even at the bands below the main line.
  

25
00:02:15,165 --> 00:02:20,045
This strategy can be applied to all 
timeframes, making it versatile for  

26
00:02:20,045 --> 00:02:25,325
both day traders, and swing traders.
The principle remains the same:  

27
00:02:25,325 --> 00:02:32,445
identify the trend, anchor the VWAP at a 
high volume bar, and trade the pullbacks.
  

28
00:02:32,445 --> 00:02:38,205
To enhance the effectiveness of this 
strategy, you can also use the VWAP bands. 

29
00:02:38,205 --> 00:02:42,925
These bands are typically set at 
one, or two standard deviations,  

30
00:02:42,925 --> 00:02:48,525
above and below the VWAP line.
They can help confirm the strength of the trend,  

31
00:02:48,525 --> 00:02:55,005
and provide additional support and resistance 
levels. When price stays consistently above the  

32
00:02:55,005 --> 00:03:02,205
upper VWAP band, it suggests a strong uptrend.
Price consistently below the lower band  

33
00:03:02,205 --> 00:03:07,405
indicates a strong downtrend.
 
These VWAP bands can also help in  

34
00:03:07,405 --> 00:03:12,685
identifying potential reversal points.
If the price has been trending strongly,  

35
00:03:12,685 --> 00:03:20,285
and suddenly penetrates the opposite VWAP band, 
it might signal a potential trend reversal.
  

36
00:03:20,285 --> 00:03:25,645
The Anchored VWAP strategy aligns well 
with the concept of trend following. 

37
00:03:25,645 --> 00:03:30,365
By anchoring the VWAP at this 
significant point and trading pullbacks,  

38
00:03:30,365 --> 00:03:35,725
you're essentially trying to catch waves 
in the direction of the overall trend. 
  

39
00:03:35,725 --> 00:03:40,525
But, VWAP, even when anchored, 
is still a lagging indicator. 

40
00:03:40,525 --> 00:03:45,965
It's based on historical price and volume 
data, which means it can't predict future  

41
00:03:45,965 --> 00:03:50,125
price movements with certainty.
That’s why, another factor to  

42
00:03:50,125 --> 00:03:55,965
consider is the overall market context.
This Anchored VWAP strategy tends to  

43
00:03:55,965 --> 00:04:01,005
work best in trending markets.
In sideways or choppy markets,  

44
00:04:01,005 --> 00:04:09,405
the pullbacks to VWAP might not be as reliable. 
 
Volume analysis must complement this strategy. 

45
00:04:09,405 --> 00:04:15,805
Not only volume is important for selecting the 
anchoring point, but it's also key for confirming  

46
00:04:15,805 --> 00:04:22,525
the strength of pullbacks and potential breakouts.
When a pullback to the Anchored VWAP occurs on  

47
00:04:22,525 --> 00:04:27,245
low volume, it often implies a 
weak retracement and a higher  

48
00:04:27,245 --> 00:04:33,725
probability that the main trend will continue.
But if the pullback happens on high volume,  

49
00:04:33,725 --> 00:04:39,965
it might indicate a stronger move, that 
could potentially break the VWAP level.
  

50
00:04:39,965 --> 00:04:45,165
To further refine your entries using this 
strategy, pay attention to price action  

51
00:04:45,165 --> 00:04:49,085
around the Anchored VWAP.
Look for rejection candles,  

52
00:04:49,085 --> 00:04:55,165
or other signs that the price is respecting 
the VWAP as a support or resistance level. 

53
00:04:55,165 --> 00:04:59,725
These could include candles with 
long wicks or engulfing bars.
  

54
00:05:00,365 --> 00:05:04,205
You might also use traditional 
support and resistance levels,  

55
00:05:04,205 --> 00:05:08,605
or even trend lines in conjunction 
with the Anchored VWAP. 

56
00:05:08,605 --> 00:05:12,525
This approach can provide 
additional confirmation.
  

57
00:05:12,525 --> 00:05:17,645
One approach to setting stop losses with this 
strategy, is to place them beyond the recent swing  

58
00:05:17,645 --> 00:05:24,205
high or low, on the other side of the VWAP.
For profit targets, you might look at  

59
00:05:24,205 --> 00:05:29,085
previous support or resistance 
levels, or at the next bands. 
  

60
00:05:29,085 --> 00:05:33,565
The Anchored VWAP strategy can be 
particularly effective when combined  

61
00:05:33,565 --> 00:05:38,765
with a multiple timeframe analysis.
For instance, you might use a higher  

62
00:05:38,765 --> 00:05:45,805
timeframe to determine the overall trend, and 
to select your anchoring point for the VWAP. 

63
00:05:45,805 --> 00:05:50,845
Then, you could drop down to a lower 
timeframe, to fine-tune your entries  

64
00:05:50,845 --> 00:05:56,205
based on pullbacks to the VWAP.
 
We’re looking at an hourly chart  

65
00:05:56,205 --> 00:06:02,685
of a stock that has been in a strong uptrend.
You notice this bar with exceptionally high  

66
00:06:02,685 --> 00:06:10,525
volume, which coincides with a strong upward move.
This seems like a good place to anchor your VWAP. 

67
00:06:10,525 --> 00:06:16,205
Over the next few days, the stock continues 
to rise, but then starts to pull back. 

68
00:06:16,205 --> 00:06:22,045
As the price approaches the Anchored VWAP 
line, you see this previous support level,  

69
00:06:22,045 --> 00:06:29,085
suggesting buyers are stepping in at this level.
This could be a good opportunity to enter a long  

70
00:06:29,085 --> 00:06:34,845
position, with a stop loss placed 
